 **##  Introduction

As a non-profit organization, investments in both time and financial resources are limited. This marketing plan shows how the investment of resources will help us achieve the outcomes in the Revv52 Strategic Plan and market the 2022/23 70th anniversary of Revv52 as an organization. 

The Key to any marketing plan is to understand clearly what the goals and objectives are as an outcome for our marketing activities. At the end of the marketing plan are a number of general indicators of the success of some of the marketing activities. 

- **Financial Measures** - Be seen and heard as a performance group
	- Bums in Seats - Our first objective is to have sold at least 90% of all seats for the season..
	- Eyes on Videos - The next objective is to get our YouTube revenue back up to at least $500 for the fiscal year.
	- Public Donations - Get $5,000 in public donations through website
- **Revv52 Member Participation** - A key risk that has occurred over the past few years is that the membership and people doing the bulk of the work have also been members of the Revv52 board.  This year’s primary goal will be to reduce the board membership to the chair + a backup and add 6-9 members to participate in one or more of three committees. There will be a focus on finding training opportunities for each group to help members develop skills to be more confident in doing the work.
    
- **Objectives aligned to Strategic Goals** - For further details on the specific marketing initiatives please see the Alignment to Revv52 Strategic Plan section.
	- Increasing Diversity and Discovery 
	    - 30% the number of submitted audition videos from last year
		- One post/month with culturally diverse groups
    - Enhancing Collaboration and Relationships
	    - Cross post with two external organizations each month
	    - Engagement Marketing - Applause rate, Amplification rate based on 2-4 engagement actions/month
    - Member Development
		- Provide opportunities for members to provide content for one or more marketing channels aligned to the marketing plan

