## Measuring Success

Key to the success of any marketing plan is understanding leading and lagging indicators that signal the success of a particular channel and campaign.  In early 2020, Google Tag Manager was added to the Revv52 website as well as the Taylor Center ticketing site.  This will allow Revv to trace which marketing channel fans who purchase tickets are coming from.   

We also have Google Analytics and (hopefully) HootSuite subscription to pull information from our website, YouTube, Facebook, Twitter and Mailchimp. This will allow us to understand how each of these channels is getting us to our goals.

The beginning of the marketing plan started with some lagging measures of success. The following are a list of more leading measures of success that will (hopefully) influence the ultimate measures of success. 

### Awareness

Awareness is looking to see what kind of attention Revv52 gets in a particular campaign. This is a combination of things but as an experiment here are three measures that look at how our audience is growing as well as our potential reach.

|   |   |   |
|---|---|---|
|Measure|Formula|Target|
|Audience Growth Rate|Net New Followers/Total Audience||
|Post Reach|Post Reach/Total Followers||
|Potential Reach|Mentions * # Followers of that Account||

### Engagement

How people are interacting with our content is our indicator of level of engagement. Applause is simply the number of followers who liked our content. Amplification is how many people share some of our social media content which then gets us into their audiences. Finally, there is a ‘virality’ metric that tracks how many unique views we’re getting from the shares with our audience.

|   |   |   |
|---|---|---|
|Measure|Formula|Target|
|Applause Rate|Approval Actions/Total Followers||
|Amplification Rate|Post Shares/Total Followers||
|Virality|# Shares/ # of Unique Impressions||

### Conversion

In the traditional sense, ‘Conversion’ is how many people purchased our product. With virtual productions, the conversion of our campaign into views is embedded within the Engagement stats above. When we get to sell tickets or other merchandise, then conversion becomes more meaningful. That said, there are a few stats to track no matter what:

|   |   |   |
|---|---|---|
|Measure|Formula|Target|
|Cost/Click|Spend/Measured Click||
|Cost/Impression|CPM = Cost per thousand impressions||**